<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="407" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1882" class="Reptilia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperolius variegatus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Hyperolius variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peters, W [CH]" journalOrPublisher="Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="8 - 10" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7796069" refId="B162" refString="Peters, W[CH], 1882a. Ueber neue Batrachier der Gattung Hyperolius und Limnodytes (Hylorana) aus Africa. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin 1882: 8 - 10, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7796069" title="Ueber neue Batrachier der Gattung Hyperolius und Limnodytes (Hylorana) aus Africa." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/7796069" volume="1882" year="1882 a">Peters (1882a)</bibRefCitation>
from an unknown number of specimens originating from &quot;Mocambique (Cabaḉeira, Quellimane, Inhambane)&quot;. 
<bibRefCitation author="Peters, W [CH]" journalOrPublisher="Reimer, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B163" refString="Peters, W[CH], 1882b. Zoologie III. Amphibien. Naturwissenschaftliche Reise nach Mozambique auf Befehl seiner Majestaet des Koenigs Friedrich Wilhelm IV. in den Jahren 1842 bis 1848 ausgefuehrt von Wilhelm C. H. Peters. G. Reimer, Berlin" title="Zoologie III. Amphibien. Naturwissenschaftliche Reise nach Mozambique auf Befehl seiner Majestaet des Koenigs Friedrich Wilhelm IV. in den Jahren 1842 bis 1848 ausgefuehrt von Wilhelm C. H. Peters. G." year="1882 b">Peters (1882b</bibRefCitation>
: 168) mentions that he first saw small specimens of this species on bushes on the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Cabaceira”">&quot;Cabaceira&quot;</normalizedToken>
peninsula in June 1843, an adult specimen on a mulberry tree in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Quellimane”">&quot;Quellimane&quot;</normalizedToken>
in January 1846. He also lists an observation from &quot;Prazo [estate] Boror&quot; in March 1846, but did not mention the locality 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Inhambane”">&quot;Inhambane&quot;</normalizedToken>
in this second publication. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tornier, G" journalOrPublisher="Dietrich Reimer, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/36023744" refId="B216" refString="Tornier, G, 1896. Reptilien und Amphibien. (Kriechthiere.). In: Moebius K (Ed.) Deutsch-Ost-Afrika. Wissenschaftliche Forschungsresultate ueber Land und Leute unseres ostafrikanischen Schutzgebietes und der angrenzenden Laender (Vol. III). Die Thierwelt Ost-Afrikas und der Nachbargebiete. Wirbelthiere (Part 3). Dietrich Reimer, Berlin, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/36023744" title="Reptilien und Amphibien. (Kriechthiere.). In: Moebius K (Ed.) Deutsch-Ost-Afrika. Wissenschaftliche Forschungsresultate ueber Land und Leute unseres ostafrikanischen Schutzgebietes und der angrenzenden Laender (Vol. III). Die Thierwelt Ost-Afrikas und der Nachbargebiete. Wirbelthiere (Part 3)." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/36023744" year="1896">Tornier (1896</bibRefCitation>
: 145, pl. 4, figs 61, 62) mentioned and depicted the two syntypes from &quot;Quellimane, Mozambique&quot;, both inventoried together under ZMB 4530. These could not be traced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer, AM" editor="Bauer, AM" journalOrPublisher="C. H. Peters (1815 - 1883). Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="39 - 81" refId="B21" refString="Bauer, AM, Guenther, R, Klipfel, M, 1995. Synopsis of taxa. In: Bauer, AM, Guenther, R, Klipfel, M, Eds., Herpetological Contributions of W. C.H. Peters (1815-1883). Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford: 39 - 81" title="Synopsis of taxa." volumeTitle="Herpetological Contributions of W." year="1995">Bauer et al. (1995</bibRefCitation>
: 46), nor by us. The other syntype(s) from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Inhambane”">&quot;Inhambane&quot;</normalizedToken>
with unknown inventory number could also not be located. 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurent, RF" journalOrPublisher="Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="65 - 96" refId="B113" refString="Laurent, RF, 1961. Note sur les Hyperolius et quelques Afrixalus (Salientia) du Musee de Berlin. Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 64 (1-2): 65 - 96" title="Note sur les Hyperolius et quelques Afrixalus (Salientia) du Musee de Berlin." volume="64" year="1961">Laurent (1961</bibRefCitation>
: 67) suggested that one of the specimens under 10249 is actually a specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bianconi" baseAuthorityYear="1849" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Afrixalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afrixalus fornasini" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fornasini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Afrixalus fornasini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bianconi, 1849). Our examinations revealed that ZMB 10249 und ZMB 75602 are 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. marmoratus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas ZMB 75603 and ZMB 75604 are juvenile specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laurent" authorityYear="1944" class="Amphibia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Afrixalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afrixalus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Afrixalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Identification on the species level was not possible for the latter two frogs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
